  "text": "Real-life problems are often ambiguous, complex and devoid of clear answers. Risk avoidance can result in a person being reluctant to innovate [CITATION_1] . Conversely, people willing to take risk are more likely to be innovative [CITATION_2] . It takes confidence and risk-taking on the part of the innovator to get a creative idea to mature to the implementation or innovation stage [CITATION_3] ).",
